  "prompt": "My girlfriend for 4years cheated 3 times. I found out 2 month ago. She started talking to a guy as a friend. He called her babe, what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through such a difficult time. It sounds like a complicated and emotionally charged situation. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Evaluate Your Feelings:** Take some time to reflect on how you feel about the relationship and whether you can continue to trust your girlfriend after repeated instances of cheating.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly:** It's important to have an honest and open conversation with your girlfriend about your feelings, concerns, and boundaries. Express how the cheating has affected you and discuss the nature of her relationship with the new guy.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries:** If you decide to stay together, establish clear boundaries regarding appropriate behavior with others. Make sure both of you agree on what is acceptable and what is not.\n\n4. **Seek Counseling:** Sometimes, talking to a professional can help both of you navigate these complex emotions and issues. Couples therapy can provide a neutral space to work through trust issues and communication problems.\n\n5. **Consider Your Options:** Ultimately, you need to decide whether you can rebuild trust and whether this relationship is healthy for you. If you feel that the relationship is causing you more harm than good, it might be time to consider moving on.\n\nRemember, your well-being is the most important thing. Make sure to take care of yourself and prioritize your mental and emotional health.",
